1. Insurance companies want to verify the legitimacy of claims by ensuring the patient was sober at the time of incident to prevent fraudulent claims.
2. The insurance companies are trying to minimize medical payments by denying claims that involve intoxication, which is a preventable cause of medical expenses.
3. Following-up to confirm sobriety may help reduce medical payments by identifying patients who were intoxicated at the time of incident and reducing the likelihood of claim reimbursement.